sentences.en: Arnold kept telling her how attractive she was, but he spread the butter too thick and she was unimpressed.
sentences.cn: 阿诺德不断对她说她如何有吸引力, 但他的诌媚过头了,其实她相貌平平.

sentences.en: Eduard Bos , a population expert at the World Bank, is unimpressed.
sentences.cn: 世界银行的人口专家 EduardBos 觉得没多神奇.

sentences.en: Graham Fletcher was unimpressed with the idea of filling in a lengthy questionnaire.
sentences.cn: 格雷厄姆·弗莱彻对填写冗长的调查问卷这种事没什么兴趣。

sentences.en: He was also very unimpressed by his teachers.
sentences.cn: 他对他的老师也很不以为然。

sentences.en: In time his reputation may recover somewhat, but locals are unimpressed.
sentences.cn: 他的名声最后可能有所恢复, 但当地人不为所动.

sentences.en: Kitty's family was unworldly, unimpressed by power, or money.
sentences.cn: 基蒂一家清心寡欲，淡泊金钱与权力。

sentences.en: Margaret was either unaware or, as is more probable, unimpressed by such convention.
sentences.cn: 也许玛格丽特不懂这种规矩,或者很可能对这种规矩不满意.

sentences.en: Only the Don was unimpressed, shrugging his shoulders and remarking , " What's the difference? "
sentences.cn: 只有老头子无动于衷, 一面耸肩一面评说: “ 有什么两样? ”

sentences.en: The bank is unimpressed by the idea of selling loans on to other investors.
sentences.cn: 在该银行的记忆中,从未有过向其它投资者发放贷款.

sentences.en: Thoreau usually remained alone unimpressed by the ideas or actions of others.
sentences.cn: 索洛孤傲自处,对他人的思想与行为毫无所动.

trans.tran_cn: 印象平平的，无深刻印象的，未被打动的
trans.tran_en: not thinking that someone or something is good, interesting etc
